Rating: 0
Here in Italy, this recipe is well-known as a warm pasta sauce, beginning with oil, garlic, anchovies, then tomatoes, green and black olives and capers. Hot chili is also welcome. Generally used with spaghetti, linguine and bucatini. A CLASSIC !!

Rating: 4
Quick, easy, and delicious! Being a grad student on a pretty tight food budget, I used canned tomatoes and dried spices, and it still had fantastic flavor. I allowed the sauce to sit in the frige and blend its flavors overnight, and then threw it in a frying pan with day-old rice to make a quick and easy Mediterranean-style stir fry.

Rating: 4
Very Flavorful! Extremely fast; I choose to use pasta not rice. It is good hot or cold, or with added seafood. I have blended in the food processor and used it as a dip on crusty bread. Think about omitting the salt, olives have enough as it is.

